  "cooked": "<p>I did work on a new approach where we do the signature verification on a blinded key, such that we can move the heavy EC operations outside the ZK environment (see the discussion here: <a href=\"https://github.com/halseth/output-zero/issues/10\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">(EDITED) following README example - slower proving time? \u00b7 Issue #10 \u00b7 halseth/output-zero \u00b7 GitHub</a>).</p>\n<p>This results in the SHA-512 hashing in verifying the utreexo proof dominating the runtime:</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e4773c123ec96b9f894d3f026195509707e5bd14.png\" data-download-href=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/e4773c123ec96b9f894d3f026195509707e5bd14\" title=\"Screenshot 2025-02-18 at 16.29.05\"><img src=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e4773c123ec96b9f894d3f026195509707e5bd14_2_690x200.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2025-02-18 at 16.29.05\" data-base62-sha1=\"wB6jZ23wVcxSMv36yinfX0UmefG\" width=\"690\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e4773c123ec96b9f894d3f026195509707e5bd14_2_690x200.png, https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e4773c123ec96b9f894d3f026195509707e5bd14_2_1035x300.png 1.5x, https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e4773c123ec96b9f894d3f026195509707e5bd14_2_1380x400.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"D0CCC3\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2025-02-18 at 16.29.05</span><span class=\"informations\">1426\u00d7415 66.3 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p><a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/davidson\">@Davidson</a> How easy is it to either</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Switch to using the <code>poseidon2</code> hash function for this, OR</li>\n<li>use the Risc0 precompile for SHA-512 (it looks like rustreexo is using the <code>bitcoin_hashes::Sha512</code> implementation).</li>\n</ol>",
